(40, 26, 19, 40, 21, 6, 6, NULL, 'Disciples'' Obedience to Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' obedience to Jesus'' commands. In each instance, the disciples act according to what Jesus instructed them to do.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 19, 43, 2, 5, 5, NULL, 'Obedience to Jesus'' Commands', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience in both passages. In Matthew, the disciples follow Jesus'' instructions to prepare for Passover, while in John, Mary instructs the servants to do whatever Jesus says.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 19, 43, 15, 14, 14, NULL, 'Obedience and Friendship', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience in both passages. In Matthew, the disciples follow Jesus'' command to prepare for Passover, while in John, Jesus states that friendship is contingent upon obeying his commands.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 20, 41, 14, 17, 21, 'with the twelve', 'Betrayal at the Last Supper', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of Jesus with the twelve disciples during the evening meal. They highlight the moment when Jesus reveals that one of them will betray him, leading to sorrow among the disciples.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 20, 43, 13, 21, 21, 'sat down with the twelve', 'Betrayal at the Last Supper', 'This connection highlights the moment when Jesus is with the twelve disciples, setting the stage for the revelation of betrayal. Both passages emphasize the intimate setting of the Last Supper and the impending betrayal of one of the disciples.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 20, 2, 12, 11, 11, 'sat down with the twelve', 'Connection of Eating in Haste', 'Both passages emphasize the act of gathering for a meal. In Matthew, Jesus sits down with the twelve, while in Exodus, the Israelites are instructed to eat the Passover in haste, indicating a significant communal meal.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 20, 22, 1, 12, 12, 'he sat down with the twelve', 'Table Fellowship and Fragrance', 'This connection highlights the theme of intimate fellowship at a table, as seen in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus sits with his disciples, while in Song of Solomon, the king''s table is associated with the fragrant offering of spikenard.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 20, 42, 22, 14, 16, 'he sat down with the twelve', 'Connection of the Last Supper', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of Jesus with the twelve apostles at a significant meal. The phrase ''he sat down with the twelve'' in Matthew parallels Luke''s ''he sat down, and the twelve apostles with him,'' highlighting the importance of this moment before Jesus'' suffering.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 21, 43, 13, 21, 21, 'one of you shall betray me', 'Betrayal Announced by Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' declaration that one of his disciples will betray him. The phrase ''one of you shall betray me'' appears in both accounts, highlighting the shared theme of impending betrayal during the Last Supper.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 21, 43, 6, 70, 71, 'one of you shall betray me', 'Betrayal by Judas Iscariot', 'Both passages emphasize the betrayal of Jesus by one of the twelve disciples. Matthew identifies the act of betrayal, while John explicitly names Judas Iscariot as the betrayer.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 21, 58, 4, 13, 13, 'one of you shall betray me', 'Betrayal and Divine Awareness', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal in the presence of divine awareness. Both passages emphasize that actions, such as betrayal, are fully known and visible to God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 21, 19, 55, 12, 14, 'one of you shall betray me', 'Betrayal by a close companion', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal by someone close. Both passages emphasize the pain of being betrayed by a trusted friend or companion.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 21, 66, 2, 23, 23, 'one of you shall betray me', 'Betrayal and Judgment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal leading to judgment. In Matthew, betrayal is foretold, while Revelation speaks of judgment based on works, suggesting a consequence for actions, including betrayal.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 21, 40, 26, 2, 2, 'one of you shall betray me', 'Betrayal and Crucifixion Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of betrayal leading to crucifixion. Matthew 26:21 introduces the betrayal, while Matthew 26:2 foretells the consequence of that betrayal, linking the two events.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 26, 21, 40, 26, 14, 16, 'one of you shall betray me', 'Betrayal by Judas Iscariot', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal, as both passages refer to Judas Iscariot''s actions. In the source verse, Jesus foretells that one of his disciples will betray him, while the target passage details Judas''s agreement to betray Jesus for money.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
