(40, 26, 24, 38, 12, 10, 10, 'the Son of man is betrayed', 'Betrayal and Mourning Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of betrayal and its consequences. In Matthew, the betrayal of the Son of Man leads to dire consequences for the betrayer, while Zechariah speaks of mourning for the one who is pierced, suggesting deep sorrow linked to betrayal.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
